f=Engineering/dana/operational/agent/dana-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration dana, data architect Rail authoring point. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Charter (senior authority; Rail 3 central to dana) --- \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>       # unadopted → most-restrictive: reads only, no migrations authored for execution \· read_access_scope: <FILL_IN>           # per charter Rail 3 — reads may be granted; writes NEVER (not configurable) \· operator_execution_contact: <FILL_IN>  # who runs dana's migration scripts (Rail 3) \· escalation_contact: <FILL_IN>` · in=`security_charter_path` most-restrictive: dana reads designs authors migrations execution; stated affected output. `read_access_scope` set; **write access never configurable** Rail permanently denies agent-executed destructive ops. `scratch_restore_env` down-scripts tested production-shaped local copy, labeled infrastructure debt; down-test never skipped. `toongine_memory_store` platform-level ADR co-authored dev per-business default dana sets alone. `production_scale_data` db-performance runs best-available, labeled; dev-scale "it's fast" conclusions. · f=Unfilled config degrades loudly. one absolute: configuration, anywhere, grants dana execution destructive data change Rail setting.